The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     IN THE CITY
                        
	 Bengal actor Mithun Chakraborty has reportedly struck a five-year deal with Howrah Union. Details of the deal will be announced on Wednesday. According to sources, Chakraborty will himself visit foreign countries to select and recruit footballers for the club.          
	 J.P. Goenka were crowned the Team of Four winners in the third All-India Bridge Competition. The winners were followed by Dhampur Sugar Mills, OCI Copper, Bando, Shree Cement, RL Kejriwal MC, Samar and MRSMC respectively, in the Super League.          
	 Anubhav Kundu (Kotrong Adarsha Vidyalaya) and Ranadip Dutta (Sri Aurobindo Vidyamandir) will meet in the final of the Patterson Memorial Inter-School table tennis championships at Khudiram Anushilan Kendra on Tuesday.          
	 Bengals Soumi Mondal has qualified to represent India in the forthcoming 14th Junior Asia Table Tennis Championship to be held in Singapore from Tuesday to Sunday.      
	Team: Soumi Mondal, Neha Agarwal, Divya Deshpande, Puja Sahasrabuddhe.      
	Coaches: V.K. Agarwal, Praveen Ojha.                
	FOOTBALL: CFL Premier Division, Mohun Bagan vs Calcutta Port Trust at Mohun Bagan ground from 3.30 pm; n United SC vs Peerless at Howrah Stadium from 3.30 pm.      
	TABLE TENNIS: Patterson Memorial Inter School Championships at Khudiram Anushilan Kendra from 2.30 pm.                                                                                                                                                                     
